# -*- encoding: utf-8 -*-
# Arc: WarriorPath | Scene: WarriorQueen5
# Source: C:\Program Files (x86)\Steam\steamapps\common\The Survival of Sarah Rose\game\script.rpy

translate ru strings:

    old "Nearly a week had passed."
    new "Nearly a week had passed."

    old "Sarah had witnessed ship after ship arrive on the shores."
    new "Sarah had witnessed ship after ship arrive on the shores."

    old "Countless soldiers. Supplies. Weapons."
    new "Countless soldiers. Supplies. Weapons."

    old "The logistics alone were a nightmare, and the fighting had hardly begun."
    new "The logistics alone were a nightmare, and the fighting had hardly begun."

    old "But with each passing day, Sarah could see the transformation."
    new "But with each passing day, Sarah could see the transformation."

    old "Her army, growing, swelling."
    new "Her army, growing, swelling."

    old "Her own mercenaries were the quickest to prepare."
    new "Her own mercenaries were the quickest to prepare."

    old "Seasoned soldiers, many had lived through at least more than one campaign."
    new "Seasoned soldiers, many had lived through at least more than one campaign."

    old "Among them, also her countryman."
    new "Among them, also her countryman."

    old "Common men, some nobles. Less trained at war, but here because they believed in the cause."
    new "Common men, some nobles. Less trained at war, but here because they believed in the cause."

    old "They would be veterans soon enough, Sarah thought."
    new "They would be veterans soon enough, Sarah thought."

    old "And lastly, the Legions of Mythra. Two of them, provided by Gilead himself."
    new "And lastly, the Legions of Mythra. Two of them, provided by Gilead himself."

    old "Each counting at five-thousand men, they stood in perfect formation."
    new "Each counting at five-thousand men, they stood in perfect formation."

    old "A show of force that made clear why the Mythran Empire had gone on to conquer most of the world."
    new "A show of force that made clear why the Mythran Empire had gone on to conquer most of the world."

    old "Sarah counted them up and wondered if they'd be enough."
    new "Sarah counted them up and wondered if they'd be enough."

    old "For the first time, she wondered if she'd made a mistake by rejecting Gilead's support."
    new "For the first time, she wondered if she'd made a mistake by rejecting Gilead's support."

    old "An extra two legions would have made all the difference."
    new "An extra two legions would have made all the difference."

    old "What had been done was done. This was the army she had. It would have to do."
    new "What had been done was done. This was the army she had. It would have to do."

    old "It had to."
    new "It had to."

    old "Studying her army from up high, she kept turning it over in her mind."
    new "Studying her army from up high, she kept turning it over in her mind."

    old "With each turn, she tried to convince herself it would be enough."
    new "With each turn, she tried to convince herself it would be enough."

    old "All day, there had been an endless series of meetings."
    new "All day, there had been an endless series of meetings."

    old "The closer they were getting to being ready, the more people needed from her."
    new "The closer they were getting to being ready, the more people needed from her."

    old "Final approval on this, a report on shortages of that, on and on."
    new "Final approval on this, a report on shortages of that, on and on."

    old "It was only late in the day when the sun had already begun to set when a loud horn rang out."
    new "It was only late in the day when the sun had already begun to set when a loud horn rang out."

    old "The sound, deep, seemed to reverberate into her bones."
    new "The sound, deep, seemed to reverberate into her bones."

    old "Sarah felt the pace of her heart quicken."
    new "Sarah felt the pace of her heart quicken."

    old "Only the sentries had these horns."
    new "Only the sentries had these horns."

    old "If they were sounding them, that meant danger."
    new "If they were sounding them, that meant danger."

    old "No sooner had she drawn her conclusion, when a young man stumbled as he ran up to her."
    new "No sooner had she drawn her conclusion, when a young man stumbled as he ran up to her."

    old "Soldier\" \"The sentries are reporting riders!"
    new "Soldier\" \"The sentries are reporting riders!"

    old "Riders?"
    new "Riders?"

    old "Soldiers\" \"Tribesmen they think."
    new "Soldiers\" \"Tribesmen they think."

    old "Is there an attack?"
    new "Is there an attack?"

    old "Soldier\" \"No, Commander. There are not enough for an attack, and they're riding straight for camp."
    new "Soldier\" \"No, Commander. There are not enough for an attack, and they're riding straight for camp."

    old "Soldier\" \"They think it might be an emissary."
    new "Soldier\" \"They think it might be an emissary."

    old "Thank you for the report, go back to your station."
    new "Thank you for the report, go back to your station."

    old "With a wave of her hand, she dismissed the young soldier."
    new "With a wave of her hand, she dismissed the young soldier."

    old "Sarah began to make her way towards the entrance of the camp."
    new "Sarah began to make her way towards the entrance of the camp."

    old "As she marched through the thick snow, she tried to process all of this."
    new "As she marched through the thick snow, she tried to process all of this."

    old "Clearly, they had been detected, but it was not the attack she had feared."
    new "Clearly, they had been detected, but it was not the attack she had feared."

    old "A message then, but what it was it remained to be seen."
    new "A message then, but what it was it remained to be seen."

    old "As the gate to the warcamp was opened, a massive black steed rode through."
    new "As the gate to the warcamp was opened, a massive black steed rode through."

    old "Mounted atop the black steed, a man equal in stature. Larger than any she had ever seen."
    new "Mounted atop the black steed, a man equal in stature. Larger than any she had ever seen."

    old "A suit of full armor covered his body, making him appear even more dangerous."
    new "A suit of full armor covered his body, making him appear even more dangerous."

    old "Sarah shuddered at the idea of anyone having to fight a man like this."
    new "Sarah shuddered at the idea of anyone having to fight a man like this."

    old "His great black steed slowed until it came to a stop."
    new "His great black steed slowed until it came to a stop."

    old "The man atop it turned his head, looking around the camp."
    new "The man atop it turned his head, looking around the camp."

    old "All around, men had stopped to take note of this dreaded arrival."
    new "All around, men had stopped to take note of this dreaded arrival."

    old "Sarah tried to look at the man, but his full plated helmet covered all of his face."
    new "Sarah tried to look at the man, but his full plated helmet covered all of his face."

    old "Finally, his head turned and his gaze locked on her."
    new "Finally, his head turned and his gaze locked on her."

    old "Tell me, who send you?"
    new "Tell me, who send you?"

    old "Emmissary\" \"Kamal, governor of Rosayi, province of the Tribal lands."
    new "Emmissary\" \"Kamal, governor of Rosayi, province of the Tribal lands."

    old "Emmissary\" \"I come bearing a message."
    new "Emmissary\" \"I come bearing a message."

    old "Sarah remembered that name from the reports. That is what the Tribes called her homeland."
    new "Sarah remembered that name from the reports. That is what the Tribes called her homeland."

    old "She would put that right soon enough too."
    new "She would put that right soon enough too."

    old "I know of no lands by such name, but I shall receive any message that you may have, though be it from a false conqueror."
    new "I know of no lands by such name, but I shall receive any message that you may have, though be it from a false conqueror."

    old "The man atop the steed reached into the saddles on the side and pulled something out."
    new "The man atop the steed reached into the saddles on the side and pulled something out."

    old "Before Sarah realized it, the man had thrown the two objects towards her."
    new "Before Sarah realized it, the man had thrown the two objects towards her."

    old "The heads landed with a loud thud, rolling as they did, leaving traces of blood in the snow."
    new "The heads landed with a loud thud, rolling as they did, leaving traces of blood in the snow."

    old "Finally, the heads finished rolling when they came to her feet."
    new "Finally, the heads finished rolling when they came to her feet."

    old "Sarah did her best not to show her shock."
    new "Sarah did her best not to show her shock."

    old "Yet, a part of her was confused as she took in the sight."
    new "Yet, a part of her was confused as she took in the sight."

    old "These were heads, but judging by their features, they were clearly Tribesmen."
    new "These were heads, but judging by their features, they were clearly Tribesmen."

    old "You threaten me?"
    new "You threaten me?"

    old "Emmissary\" \"I bear no threats. Only gifts."
    new "Emmissary\" \"I bear no threats. Only gifts."

    old "What am I to do with gifts such as these?"
    new "What am I to do with gifts such as these?"

    old "Emmissary\" \"They are my gift to you, Princess of Rosanna."
    new "Emmissary\" \"They are my gift to you, Princess of Rosanna."

    old "Emmissary\" \"And let it be known to all who shall hear that the first blood of this war was spilled by me, in your honour."
    new "Emmissary\" \"And let it be known to all who shall hear that the first blood of this war was spilled by me, in your honour."

    old "Sarah felt her eyes go wide. The voice...something about his voice..."
    new "Sarah felt her eyes go wide. The voice...something about his voice..."

    old "Emmissary\" \"I carry many names. Kinslayer. Widowmaker. Exile."
    new "Emmissary\" \"I carry many names. Kinslayer. Widowmaker. Exile."

    old "His voice boomed louder and louder."
    new "His voice boomed louder and louder."

    old "Emmissary\" \"But you need not waste breath on honours or titles. You may name me as you know me."
    new "Emmissary\" \"But you need not waste breath on honours or titles. You may name me as you know me."

    old "Sarah felt her heart pounding in her chest. It was him."
    new "Sarah felt her heart pounding in her chest. It was him."

    old "The man removed his plated helmet and threw it aside."
    new "The man removed his plated helmet and threw it aside."

    old "Atilla!"
    new "Atilla!"

    old "Sarah rushed across the open space as fast as her feet could carry her."
    new "Sarah rushed across the open space as fast as her feet could carry her."

    old "She watched as Atilla leapt from his mighty horse in one swift movement."
    new "She watched as Atilla leapt from his mighty horse in one swift movement."

    old "As she reached him, she crashed into his chest."
    new "As she reached him, she crashed into his chest."

    old "His body barely moved, despite all the force behind her."
    new "His body barely moved, despite all the force behind her."

    old "Sarah felt his massive arms wrapping around her, and she felt that safety that she had only ever found in his arms."
    new "Sarah felt his massive arms wrapping around her, and she felt that safety that she had only ever found in his arms."

    old "Come now, girl, you're making a scene."
    new "Come now, girl, you're making a scene."

    old "His voice was soft, yet deep."
    new "His voice was soft, yet deep."

    old "Sarah burried her face in his mighty chest and cried."
    new "Sarah burried her face in his mighty chest and cried."

    old "She didn't care for who saw it."
    new "She didn't care for who saw it."

    old "You're back."
    new "You're back."

    old "She spoke the words in between the sobs."
    new "She spoke the words in between the sobs."

    old "You're really back!"
    new "You're really back!"

    old "She only felt his arms tighten around her further."
    new "She only felt his arms tighten around her further."

    old "I am back."
    new "I am back."

    old "As he spoke the words, Sarah slowly allowed herself to believe it was all real. That she wasn't dreaming."
    new "As he spoke the words, Sarah slowly allowed herself to believe it was all real. That she wasn't dreaming."

    old "Atilla...I...how did you..."
    new "Atilla...I...how did you..."

    old "She had so many questions for him. So many things she wanted to ask him."
    new "She had so many questions for him. So many things she wanted to ask him."

    old "I will tell you everything, girl."
    new "I will tell you everything, girl."

    old "But perhaps we should go somewhere with fewer eyes."
    new "But perhaps we should go somewhere with fewer eyes."

    old "Sarah summoned all her power to pull away from him."
    new "Sarah summoned all her power to pull away from him."

    old "Tears still in her eyes, she nodded as she looked up at the towering figure."
    new "Tears still in her eyes, she nodded as she looked up at the towering figure."

    old "Yes, we can go to the commander's tent."
    new "Yes, we can go to the commander's tent."

    old "She began to walk, and she could hear Atilla following her, each step leaving a loud thump in the snow."
    new "She began to walk, and she could hear Atilla following her, each step leaving a loud thump in the snow."

    old "Sarah wanted to ask him so much, but she held it all in, remaining quiet as she guided him through the camp."
    new "Sarah wanted to ask him so much, but she held it all in, remaining quiet as she guided him through the camp."

    old "Finally, as she stepped into the tent that functioned as her warroom, Sarah turned around."
    new "Finally, as she stepped into the tent that functioned as her warroom, Sarah turned around."

    old "She felt herself shake with excitement as Atilla entered the tent after her."
    new "She felt herself shake with excitement as Atilla entered the tent after her."

    old "Only when it fell close, leaving just the two of them alone, did she dare to speak."
    new "Only when it fell close, leaving just the two of them alone, did she dare to speak."

    old "It's really you...I still can't believe it..."
    new "It's really you...I still can't believe it..."

    old "He grinned in that arrogant way that still left him charming to her."
    new "He grinned in that arrogant way that still left him charming to her."

    old "What did you think of my gift?"
    new "What did you think of my gift?"

    old "Two severed heads?"
    new "Two severed heads?"

    old "Not the worst gift I've ever received."
    new "Not the worst gift I've ever received."

    old "I didn't want to show up to our meeting empty-handed."
    new "I didn't want to show up to our meeting empty-handed."

    old "Did you consider flowers?"
    new "Did you consider flowers?"

    old "Atilla laughed, his voice booming."
    new "Atilla laughed, his voice booming."

    old "Who were they?"
    new "Who were they?"

    old "The other two messengers that were send along with me to deliver a message."
    new "The other two messengers that were send along with me to deliver a message."

    old "Sarah sighed in disbelief."
    new "Sarah sighed in disbelief."

    old "You killed them..."
    new "You killed them..."

    old "But you said you were send with them? I don't understand."
    new "But you said you were send with them? I don't understand."

    old "Atilla walked across the tent and sat down."
    new "Atilla walked across the tent and sat down."

    old "There is so much I want to tell you, Sarah. So much since we last saw."
    new "There is so much I want to tell you, Sarah. So much since we last saw."

    old "I'm the same...but it's been so long, I hardly know where to begin."
    new "I'm the same...but it's been so long, I hardly know where to begin."

    old "Atilla smiled."
    new "Atilla smiled."

    old "Then let me tell you..."
    new "Then let me tell you..."

    old "Atilla turned to the fireplace, quickly making a small fire, warming up the tent."
    new "Atilla turned to the fireplace, quickly making a small fire, warming up the tent."

    old "When he sat down, he looke at her, those golden, piercing eyes that only orcs possessed."
    new "When he sat down, he looke at her, those golden, piercing eyes that only orcs possessed."

    old "Sarah felt herself shifting about, nervous to be so observed, even when it was him."
    new "Sarah felt herself shifting about, nervous to be so observed, even when it was him."

    old "When you took the Exam, I had made my decision to leave the same day."
    new "When you took the Exam, I had made my decision to leave the same day."

    old "I feared that if we said our goodbyes...that I might change my mind."
    new "I feared that if we said our goodbyes...that I might change my mind."

    old "Sarah knew it had been no idle fear. She had felt the same."
    new "Sarah knew it had been no idle fear. She had felt the same."

    old "I was sad when I didn't see you after...but I understand."
    new "I was sad when I didn't see you after...but I understand."

    old "If I hurt you, I apologize..."
    new "If I hurt you, I apologize..."

    old "His voice was soft, his remorse genuine."
    new "His voice was soft, his remorse genuine."

    old "It was funny to Sarah, that there was this side to him. To the warrior. The killer."
    new "It was funny to Sarah, that there was this side to him. To the warrior. The killer."

    old "This side only she saw."
    new "This side only she saw."

    old "I left and I took up with another mercenary company."
    new "I left and I took up with another mercenary company."

    old "Sarah wasn't surprised. A man of Atilla's skills was never short for work."
    new "Sarah wasn't surprised. A man of Atilla's skills was never short for work."

    old "I fought with them for a while. Joined a merchant that needed protection. I drifted about for a long time."
    new "I fought with them for a while. Joined a merchant that needed protection. I drifted about for a long time."

    old "Wherever I went, I did my best to track down news of you. To know if you were still safe."
    new "Wherever I went, I did my best to track down news of you. To know if you were still safe."

    old "Sarah smiled. She had often dreamed, on lonely nights, about Atilla's fate. She was glad to know he had been out there, doing the same."
    new "Sarah smiled. She had often dreamed, on lonely nights, about Atilla's fate. She was glad to know he had been out there, doing the same."

    old "I had thought that if I left, it would break the bond between us...give you the space that you needed to become what I knew you could be."
    new "I had thought that if I left, it would break the bond between us...give you the space that you needed to become what I knew you could be."

    old "And in truth...I had hoped that what had begun to burn in my heart would fade when we were away from one another."
    new "And in truth...I had hoped that what had begun to burn in my heart would fade when we were away from one another."

    old "Sarah remembered. Her mind, flooded with memories."
    new "Sarah remembered. Her mind, flooded with memories."

    old "Their affair had been short lived perhaps, but it had never quite left her system."
    new "Their affair had been short lived perhaps, but it had never quite left her system."

    old "He had set a claim on her heart that she had never been able to fully remove."
    new "He had set a claim on her heart that she had never been able to fully remove."

    old "Always traces of him. Hints."
    new "Always traces of him. Hints."

    old "That had also been the danger of it, she remembered."
    new "That had also been the danger of it, she remembered."

    old "In only weeks together, Sarah had been entirely willing to betray everything."
    new "In only weeks together, Sarah had been entirely willing to betray everything."

    old "If he had asked it of her, she would have walked away from her throne. From everything."
    new "If he had asked it of her, she would have walked away from her throne. From everything."

    old "And he has seen the same in her."
    new "And he has seen the same in her."

    old "Leaving, painful as it was, had been a kindness."
    new "Leaving, painful as it was, had been a kindness."

    old "But what I felt for you...it never left me."
    new "But what I felt for you...it never left me."

    old "On dark nights and in dark dreams, you haunted my heart."
    new "On dark nights and in dark dreams, you haunted my heart."

    old "More than once, I was so close that I feared I might betray my own promise and seek you out."
    new "More than once, I was so close that I feared I might betray my own promise and seek you out."

    old "A sad smile drew on Sarah's face."
    new "A sad smile drew on Sarah's face."

    old "I wish you had...some nights."
    new "I wish you had...some nights."

    old "Atilla nodded, staring into the fire."
    new "Atilla nodded, staring into the fire."

    old "One night...after years of fighting it, I broke."
    new "One night...after years of fighting it, I broke."

    old "I gathered my things and I set out to find you."
    new "I gathered my things and I set out to find you."

    old "There was a shame in his voice. Breaking a vow was no easy thing for him."
    new "There was a shame in his voice. Breaking a vow was no easy thing for him."

    old "I only made it a few days before I arrived in Lethram and my senses came back to me."
    new "I only made it a few days before I arrived in Lethram and my senses came back to me."

    old "I spotted you from a distance, confident and strong...and I knew I had no right to take that from you."
    new "I spotted you from a distance, confident and strong...and I knew I had no right to take that from you."

    old "To rob you of your potential."
    new "To rob you of your potential."

    old "You saw me?"
    new "You saw me?"

    old "A day, more than a year ago, in Lethram. But I kept myself hidden."
    new "A day, more than a year ago, in Lethram. But I kept myself hidden."

    old "Sarah felt a sad rush come over her. She wished she had seen him. Known that he had been so close."
    new "Sarah felt a sad rush come over her. She wished she had seen him. Known that he had been so close."

    old "When my senses came back to me, I knew that I could not meet with you."
    new "When my senses came back to me, I knew that I could not meet with you."

    old "But I also knew I could not leave you, or I would suffer the same torment again."
    new "But I also knew I could not leave you, or I would suffer the same torment again."

    old "So instead, I vowed to myself to meet you when you were ready."
    new "So instead, I vowed to myself to meet you when you were ready."

    old "Ready?"
    new "Ready?"

    old "I paid a sailor to take me across the sea, from Lethram to Rosanna."
    new "I paid a sailor to take me across the sea, from Lethram to Rosanna."

    old "I entered into the service of the Tribesman Warlord known as Kamal, the governor of this place."
    new "I entered into the service of the Tribesman Warlord known as Kamal, the governor of this place."

    old "You joined the Tribesmen?"
    new "You joined the Tribesmen?"

    old "Yes. I joined them because I knew the day would come when you would face them."
    new "Yes. I joined them because I knew the day would come when you would face them."

    old "The day that your destiny would be so set that I could do nothing to distract you from it."
    new "The day that your destiny would be so set that I could do nothing to distract you from it."

    old "And until then, I vowed to weaken your enemies."
    new "And until then, I vowed to weaken your enemies."

    old "I...weaken them? By joining them?"
    new "I...weaken them? By joining them?"

    old "I am an orc, and a warrior by heart."
    new "I am an orc, and a warrior by heart."

    old "To act in such subterfuge...it did not come easy to me."
    new "To act in such subterfuge...it did not come easy to me."

    old "But I did."
    new "But I did."

    old "I murdered them in the dark. Burned their granaries. Assassinated their leaders."
    new "I murdered them in the dark. Burned their granaries. Assassinated their leaders."

    old "You...were a spy?"
    new "You...were a spy?"

    old "Atilla grunted at the word."
    new "Atilla grunted at the word."

    old "Each night I prayed for the clarity of honest combat...but I knew this would do the most to help you."
    new "Each night I prayed for the clarity of honest combat...but I knew this would do the most to help you."

    old "Help you before you arrived."
    new "Help you before you arrived."

    old "That's...actually really smart."
    new "That's...actually really smart."

    old "She saw a brief smile on Atilla's face, eager to know he had not fallen in her estimation."
    new "She saw a brief smile on Atilla's face, eager to know he had not fallen in her estimation."

    old "Then, a few days ago the report came in that an army had been discovered on the shores."
    new "Then, a few days ago the report came in that an army had been discovered on the shores."

    old "I knew it could only be you, so I volunteered to deliver the message from Kamal."
    new "I knew it could only be you, so I volunteered to deliver the message from Kamal."

    old "Two others were send with me, as for their fates...well, they made fine gifts."
    new "Two others were send with me, as for their fates...well, they made fine gifts."

    old "All that...just so you could come back to me?"
    new "All that...just so you could come back to me?"

    old "His piercing golden eyes met hers, and she felt her resolve fade like snow to fire."
    new "His piercing golden eyes met hers, and she felt her resolve fade like snow to fire."

    old "You are not the girl that I left in that mercenary camp."
    new "You are not the girl that I left in that mercenary camp."

    old "You are the woman I knew you would become."
    new "You are the woman I knew you would become."

    old "Sarah smiled. His compliments had always meant more to her than those of others."
    new "Sarah smiled. His compliments had always meant more to her than those of others."

    old "I did change a lot as well..."
    new "I did change a lot as well..."

    old "Sarah began to tell Atilla of her own years apart from him."
    new "Sarah began to tell Atilla of her own years apart from him."

    old "The battles. The campaigns. Bagrad. Everything, or at least, as much as she dared to share with him. With anyone."
    new "The battles. The campaigns. Bagrad. Everything, or at least, as much as she dared to share with him. With anyone."

    old "The hours passed as they sat by the fire."
    new "The hours passed as they sat by the fire."

    old "He listened, in that quiet, stern way that only he could."
    new "He listened, in that quiet, stern way that only he could."

    old "And Sarah found it strange how quickly they fell into their roles."
    new "And Sarah found it strange how quickly they fell into their roles."

    old "You've been gone for years...I missed you...and now it's like you never left."
    new "You've been gone for years...I missed you...and now it's like you never left."

    old "Atilla watched the fires dance."
    new "Atilla watched the fires dance."

    old "To see you like this...to speak with you again...it is like a dream."
    new "To see you like this...to speak with you again...it is like a dream."

    old "He breathed a heavy sigh."
    new "He breathed a heavy sigh."

    old "I wish I could stay longer."
    new "I wish I could stay longer."

    old "Why? You don't have to leave."
    new "Why? You don't have to leave."

    old "Atilla looked at her, tragedy in his eyes."
    new "Atilla looked at her, tragedy in his eyes."

    old "You are so much the woman that I had known you would become."
    new "You are so much the woman that I had known you would become."

    old "But you fight for your homeland now."
    new "But you fight for your homeland now."

    old "Between us...so much is the same...but the world beyond this tent..."
    new "Between us...so much is the same...but the world beyond this tent..."

    old "When they had met, she had been a fallen girl, one who had little care for reputation."
    new "When they had met, she had been a fallen girl, one who had little care for reputation."

    old "And a human woman that gave herself to an orc...such things were spoken of in only whispered insults."
    new "And a human woman that gave herself to an orc...such things were spoken of in only whispered insults."

    old "Now she was a Princess again. A Queen, if she could win her war."
